#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.0"
msgid "74. Pahārasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.74\">Monks’ Confession 74: the training rule on "
"striking</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.146
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.74.1\""
">Bu-Pc.74.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.47\">BD.3.47</a><a class"
"=\"wt-pa\">1345</a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the "
"Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā "
"sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ denti."
msgstr ""
"At that <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.146\">Vin.4.146</a> time the monks "
"from the group of six struck monks from the group of seventeen in anger."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.3"
msgid "Te rodanti."
msgstr "They cried."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks asked them why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.5"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.6"
msgid ""
"“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhākaṃ pahāraṃ dentī”ti."
msgstr "and they told them what had happened.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1346</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.9"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ "
"dassantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six strike other monks in anger?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.10"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ dethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.13"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ "
"dassatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you strike other monks in anger?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:1.1.16"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa kupito anattamano pahāraṃ dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1347</a>‘If a monk strikes another monk in anger, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.74.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.74.2.1\">Bu-Pc.74.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-"
"pa\">1348</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1349</a><term>Another monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.7"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "<gloss>a different monk.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.8"
msgid "Kupito anattamanoti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1350</a><term>In anger</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.9"
msgid "anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "<gloss>discontent, having hatred, hostile.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.10"
msgid "Pahāraṃ dadeyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1351</a><term>Strikes</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā antamaso uppalapattenapi "
"pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he strikes with his body, with something connected to his body, or "
"with <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.481\">BD.3.48</a> something released, "
"even if only with a lotus leaf, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne upasampannasaññī kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.74.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.74.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1352</a>If it is one who is fully "
"ordained, and he perceives him as fully ordained, and he strikes him in "
"anger, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne vematiko kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he "
"strikes him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully "
"ordained, and he strikes him in anger, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.4"
msgid "Anupasampannassa kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1353</a>If he strikes one who is not fully ordained in "
"anger, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.5"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive him as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.74.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.74.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1354</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"kenaci viheṭhīyamāno mokkhādhippāyo pahāraṃ deti, ummattakassa, "
"ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he is being oppressed and he strikes for the purpose of freeing himself; "
"if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc74:2.3.3"
msgid "Pahārasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1355</a>The fourth rule, the "
"training rule on striking, is finished.</p>"
